sentences.sentence:
Section 1322(6)(a) of the Act provides that the Court must not make an order under s 1322(4)(a) unless it is satisfied: (i) that the act, matter or thing, or the proceeding, referred to in that paragraph is essentially of a procedural nature;
(ii) that the person or persons concerned in or party to the contravention or failure acted honestly; or
(iii) that it is just and equitable that the order be made.
